description:
I'm trying to run this query on my instance of Virtuoso against the DBpedia Virtuoso SPARQL endpoint
SELECT ?s1 ?sc
WHERE {
  SERVICE <http://dbpedia.org/sparql> {
    SELECT ?s1 ((?sc * 3e-1) as ?sc) ?o1
    WHERE {
      ?s1 ?s1textp ?o1 .
      FILTER (CONTAINS(?o1, 'MARTIN AND LUTHER AND PRAISED'))
    }
    ORDER BY DESC(?sc + sql:rnk_scale(<LONG::IRI_RANK>(?s1)))
    LIMIT 50 OFFSET 0
  }
}

After running I receive this error message:

Virtuoso RDFZZ Error DB.DBA.SPARQL_REXEC('http://dbpedia.org/sparql', ...) returned Content-Type 'text/plain' status 'HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
Virtuoso 37000 Error SP031: SPARQL compiler: Free-text options can be specified only for triple patterns with special predicates, not for plain patterns

I'm unsure about special predicates and plain patterns, what I'm trying to achieve is to do text search similar to searching on the DBpedia endpoint but instead using their endpoint as a service.
I would appreciate any guidance. Thank you!
